summary: This is an email chain from February 18, 2020, between FBI personnel discussing logistical arrangements for an interview, including booking a conference room in Pensacola. The email includes references to attachments that appear to be related to a 2005 interview and a grand jury subpoena response.

events.title: Interview referenced in attachment
events.description: An interview conducted on November 10, 2005, referenced in an attached PDF file named '2005-11-10,a_interview PBPD.pdf'.

events.title: Email coordination for interview logistics
events.description: FBI personnel exchange emails to coordinate booking a conference room in Pensacola for an upcoming interview.

keyFacts: The email chain is dated February 18, 2020, and involves FBI personnel coordinating logistics for an interview.
An attachment references a 2005 interview document dated November 10, 2005, titled '2005-11-10,a_interview PBPD.pdf'.
Another attachment is a grand jury subpoena response document titled 'GJ_SUBPOENA_RESPONSE_000357.pdf'.
The location for the planned interview is Pensacola, where a conference room needs to be booked.
The email indicates ongoing investigative activity related to the Epstein case as of early 2020.
